<chapter xmlns   ="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
         xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
         xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
         xml:id  ="install-pcf-connector-${project.version}"
         xml:lang="en"
         version ="5.0">
  <title>${project.name} Installation Instructions</title>
  <para>
    This chapter describes how to install the ${project.name} and any prerequisites specific to its use.
  </para>
  <!--This chapter is written manually for each connector -->
  <section xml:id="before-you-install-pcf-connector-${project.version}">
    <title>Before You install the ${project.name}</title>
    <para></para>
  </section>
  <section xml:id="connector-install-pcf-connector-${project.version}">
    <title>Installing the ${project.name}</title>
    <para>
      The ${project.name} is provided in the <filename>oracle/connector/${project.artifact}-${project.version}.jar</filename>
      file, for local use. If you are running the connector remotely, copy the connector jar file to the
      <literal>bundles</literal> directory on the Java connector server.
    </para>
    <para>
      Additional configuration properties are as described in the
      <link xl:show="new"
            xl:href="CURRENT.DOCID#chapter-config-install-pcf-connector-${project.version}"
            xl:role="http://docbook.org/xl/role/olink">
        <citetitle>Configuration Chapter</citetitle>
      </link>.
    </para>
  </section>
  <section xml:id="connector-pooling-install-pcf-connector-${project.version}">
    <title>Configuring Connection Pooling</title>
    <para>
      The ${project.name} supports connection pooling, which can substantially improve the performance of the
      connector. The basic connection pooling configuration is described in the
      <link xl:show="new"
            xl:href="CURRENT.DOCID#appendix-pooling"
            xl:role="http://docbook.org/xl/role/olink">
        <citetitle>Connection Pooling Configuration Appendix</citetitle>
      </link>.
    </para>
  </section>
</chapter>